text:
New: Collectibles! 

Support your favorite creators by collecting their casts onchain. Each cast can be turned into a unique, 1-of-1 collectible. Just tap the new "collect" icon on a cast to get started. 

Casts can be collected starting at $1. If there are multiple collectors, it goes to the highest bidder. Creators get 90% collectible earnings, and the remaining 10% goes to the protocol rewards. 

We‚Äôre excited about collectibles for a few reasons: 
1. Creators earn directly from their audience
2. New creators can earn on their first day
3. Users get to collect a unique piece of Farcaster history

Collectibles will go live tomorrow morning around 9am PT. We're announcing this early so people can be ready to collect their favorite casts when the feature is live! 

Learn more here: https://farcasterhq.notion.site/Collectibles-2306a6c0c10180d7a917c24892662a3c?pvs=74

Collectibles are now live!

1. Mobile only. Update to latest mobile app / restart your app.

2. If you're on the latest app, you'll get an in-app flow to opt in or out.

3. Your casts are now eligible for collecting!

4. Remember‚Äîmost casts won't be eligible right away. It will take some time for people to opt in.

5. New cast auctions are 24 hours. Historical cast auctions are 7 days. 

6. All bids are in USDC with the Farcaster wallet.

For developers: Farcaster collectibles

1. Onchain stuff is on Base

2. Bids are USDC

3. To start, you need to use the Farcaster app + wallet to bid. And FID is required to bid.

4. Auction logic is offchain so we can iterate faster.

5. When auction ends, settlement of bids in onchain. Collectible gets created on onchain.

6. NFT is a single collection.

7. We're thinking about 1) NFT metadata 2) public APIs for auctions 3) other developer legos.

8. If collectibles is "working" (subjective, will take some time to figure this out), will figure out how to make more "protocolized" and easy for other clients that would want to add. Eventually, auction logic could also be onchain (after we're confident in the right configuration).

If you're interested in building something, reply here!
